{% comment %}
  Header Menu
  File: sections/header-menu.liquid

  Renders the desktop menu bar and the mobile nav drawer.

  Add to layout/theme.liquid, directly after {%- section 'main-header' -%}:
    {%- section 'header-menu' -%}

  Block types: single-link | link-list | mega | highlight | flyout

  `mega` is rendered fully INLINE in this file — it does not delegate to
  a separate block/snippet file, and owns its own styling/behavior pair:
    mega → assets/mega-menu.css + assets/mega-menu.js

  `flyout` delegates entirely to snippets/flyout-menu.liquid, paired with:
    assets/flyout-menu.css
    assets/flyout-menu.js
  Both `mega` and `flyout` remain real Shopify block types (see schema
  below), so "Add block" continues to offer Mega menu / Flyout panel as
  normal in the theme editor.

  The `link-list` block type is also rendered inline (no block file). It
  owns its own panel classes (.link-list-panel__*) in link-list.css.

  Assets (loaded once, here):
    assets/link-list.css
    assets/link-list.js
    assets/mega-menu.css
    assets/mega-menu.js
    assets/flyout-menu.css
    assets/flyout-menu.js

  No promo-image support on the flyout block — not currently implemented.

  REMOVED — delete these from the theme, nothing references them anymore:
    snippets/flyout.liquid
    snippets/flyout-column.liquid
    assets/flyout.css
    assets/flyout.js
    assets/flyout-panel.js
    blocks/mega-menu.liquid
    assets/header-mega-menu.css
    assets/header-mega-menu.js

  CHANGELOG (this revision):
  - FIXED (containment): `.menu-bar__container`'s class changed from
    the generic `page-width` to `page-width--header` (defined in
    base.css, using `var(--header-width)` / `var(--header-margin)`).
    Previously the menu bar used a *different* width container than the
    rest of the header (logo / search / cart), so the nav row — and
    anything positioned relative to it, including the flyout and mega
    menu panels — could be wider than the header bar above it,
    appearing to "break out" of the site's content width. Using
    `page-width--header` here guarantees the menu bar always matches
    the same width as the rest of the header, edge to edge. Pairs with
    the matching `position: relative` added to `.menu-bar__container`
    in assets/header-menu.css (needed so the full-width flyout panel
    can anchor to this exact box — see assets/flyout-menu.css) and the
    width-capping changes in assets/flyout-menu.css.
  - No markup, block schema, or Liquid logic changed beyond that single
    class swap — all block types (single-link, link-list, mega,
    highlight, flyout) and the mobile drawer render exactly as before.

  ── PRIOR CHANGELOG (earlier revision, unchanged here) ──────────────
  - ADDED: "Flyout panel style" setting (`panel_style`) to the `flyout`
    block schema, under a new "Style" header. Merchant-facing choice
    between "Compact (left-aligned)" and "Full-width span". Defaults to
    `compact`, so existing flyout blocks render exactly as before until
    a merchant explicitly switches the option. The setting is consumed
    in snippets/flyout-menu.liquid, which appends
    `flyout-panel--full-width` to the panel's class when full-width is
    selected — no other markup or section logic changed.
{% endcomment %}

